  "text": "Another source of differences is the fact that the Sone group considered females, while we acquired data from males. Studies considering gender have indicated that vertebral sizes increase significantly in men with the age but there is a lack of consensus whether vertebral body expansion occurs in women [CITATION_1] . We believe that the positive influence of h a /h p adjustment on aBMD is partially the effect of considering the age-related changes. As our samples were from males, it is impossible to make any conclusions considering a female population on the basis of our data. This is one of the largest disadvantages of the presented work, and further investigations will address this issue.",
